The paper deals with the evaluation of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and proposes a novel measure of performance based on comparing geometrical properties of the underlying data manifold and the generated one. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it deals with the evaluation of a machine learning model. Additionally, the paper mentions that the proposed algorithm can be applied to datasets of an arbitrary nature and is not limited to visual data, which suggests that it could also belong to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with the detection of mode collapse in GANs, which is a common problem in Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Statistical Learning (cs.SD) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.SD, in that order.
